HEADWORD: Oleone
<hw>O"le*one</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>oleum +
-one</ets>, 1.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>An oily liquid, obtained
by distillation of calcium oleate, and probably consisting of the ketone
of oleic acid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oleo oil</ent>⟦br⟧
